1
00:40:26,161 --> 00:40:27,954
THORIN:
We'll camp here for the night.

2
00:40:28,413 --> 00:40:32,792
Fili, Kili, look after the ponies.
Make sure you stay with them.

3
00:40:33,043 --> 00:40:37,056
A farmer and his family used to live here.

4
00:40:37,256 --> 00:40:40,017
THORIN: Oin, Gloin. Get a fire going.
OIN: Aye.

5
00:40:40,217 --> 00:40:41,226
Right you are.

6
00:40:41,426 --> 00:40:45,054
I think it would be wiser to move on.

7
00:40:46,056 --> 00:40:48,933
We could make for the Hidden Valley.

8
00:40:49,226 --> 00:40:51,070
I have told you already...

9
00:40:51,270 --> 00:40:53,113
...I will not go near that place.

10
00:40:53,313 --> 00:40:55,574
Why not? The Elves could help us.

11
00:40:55,774 --> 00:40:57,826
We could get food, rest, advice.

12
00:40:58,026 --> 00:41:00,120
THORIN:
I do not need their advice.

13
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:04,333
We have a map that we cannot read.
Lord Elrond could help us.

14
00:41:04,533 --> 00:41:05,908
Help?

15
00:41:06,952 --> 00:41:09,004
A dragon attacks Erebor.

16
00:41:09,204 --> 00:41:11,455
What help came from the Elves?

17
00:41:12,541 --> 00:41:14,426
Orcs plunder Moria...

18
00:41:14,626 --> 00:41:17,012
...desecrate our sacred halls.

19
00:41:17,212 --> 00:41:20,089
The Elves looked on and did nothing.

20
00:41:21,091 --> 00:41:25,104
And you ask me to seek out the very people
who betrayed my grandfather.

21
00:41:25,304 --> 00:41:26,563
Who betrayed my father.

22
00:41:26,763 --> 00:41:28,556
You are neither of them.

23
00:41:29,474 --> 00:41:32,903
I did not give you that map and key
for you to hold onto the past.

24
00:41:33,103 --> 00:41:35,146
I did not know that they were yours to keep.

25
00:41:41,361 --> 00:41:44,039
Everything all right?
Gandalf, where are you going?

26
00:41:44,239 --> 00:41:47,626
GANDALF: To seek the company of the
only one around here who's got any sense.

27
00:41:47,826 --> 00:41:50,494
- And who's that?
GANDALF: Myself, Mr. Baggins.

28
00:41:50,954 --> 00:41:53,456
I've had enough of Dwarves for one day.

29
00:41:55,375 --> 00:41:57,335
Come on, Bombur, we're hungry.

30
00:41:58,003 --> 00:42:00,129
Is he coming back?

31
00:42:03,133 --> 00:42:04,393
[DWARVES CHATTERING]

32
00:42:04,593 --> 00:42:05,853
He's been a long time.

33
00:42:06,053 --> 00:42:07,312
- Who?
- Gandalf.

34
00:42:07,512 --> 00:42:09,648
He's a Wizard. He does as he chooses.

35
00:42:09,848 --> 00:42:12,892
Here, do us a favor. Take this to the lads.

36
00:42:13,477 --> 00:42:14,987
Stop it. You've had plenty.

37
00:42:15,187 --> 00:42:18,782
GLOIN: Aye, it's not a bad stew, Bombur.
I've had worse.

38
00:42:18,982 --> 00:42:20,993
NORI:
Dori could've cooked it. Ha-ha-ha.

39
00:42:21,193 --> 00:42:23,444
DORI:
Hilarious.

40
00:42:34,164 --> 00:42:35,424
What's the matter?

41
00:42:35,624 --> 00:42:40,012
- We're supposed to be looking after the ponies.
- Only we've encountered a slight problem.

42
00:42:40,212 --> 00:42:42,055
KILI:
We had 16.

43
00:42:42,255 --> 00:42:45,049
FILI:
Now there's 14.

44
00:42:48,428 --> 00:42:50,689
KILI:
Daisy and Bungo are missing.

45
00:42:50,889 --> 00:42:52,649
Well, that's not good. Ha, ha.

46
00:42:52,849 --> 00:42:55,444
And that is not good at all.
Shouldn't we tell Thorin?

47
00:42:55,644 --> 00:42:58,530
Uh, no. Let's not worry him.

48
00:42:58,730 --> 00:43:01,950
As our official burglar,
we thought you might like to look into it.

49
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:03,526
Well, uh...

50
00:43:04,069 --> 00:43:08,207
- Look, something big uprooted these trees.
- That was our thinking.

51
00:43:08,407 --> 00:43:12,910
- It's something very big
and possibly quite dangerous.

52
00:43:13,745 --> 00:43:14,787
Hey.

53
00:43:15,372 --> 00:43:16,914
There's a light.

54
00:43:17,541 --> 00:43:18,958
Over here.

55
00:43:21,461 --> 00:43:22,605
Stay down.

56
00:43:24,131 --> 00:43:27,007
[GRUNTING AND LAUGHTER]

57
00:43:27,968 --> 00:43:29,353
What is it?

58
00:43:29,553 --> 00:43:30,970
Trolls.

59
00:43:49,281 --> 00:43:50,322
Oh.

60
00:43:50,532 --> 00:43:52,533
[PONIES NEIGHING]

61
00:43:57,914 --> 00:43:59,915
He's got Myrtle and Minty.

62
00:44:00,959 --> 00:44:03,720
I think they're gonna eat them.
We have to do something.

63
00:44:03,920 --> 00:44:05,713
Yes, you should.

64
00:44:06,006 --> 00:44:09,977
Mountain Trolls are slow and stupid,
and you're so small, they'll never see you.

65
00:44:10,177 --> 00:44:12,104
It's perfectly safe. We'll be behind you.

66
00:44:12,304 --> 00:44:15,899
If you run into trouble, hoot twice
like a barn owl and once like a brown owl.

67
00:44:16,099 --> 00:44:19,027
BILBO: Twice like a barn owl.
No, twice like a brown-- Once like a--

68
00:44:19,227 --> 00:44:21,187
Like a-- Are you sure this is a good idea?

69
00:44:21,563 --> 00:44:24,575
BERT:
Mutton yesterday, mutton today...

70
00:44:24,775 --> 00:44:28,277
...and, blimey, if it don't look like
mutton again tomorrow.

71
00:44:29,362 --> 00:44:31,331
WILLIAM:
Quit your griping.

72
00:44:31,531 --> 00:44:35,752
These ain't sheep. These is fresh nags.

73
00:44:35,952 --> 00:44:41,258
Oh! I don't like horse. I never have.
Not enough fat on them.

74
00:44:41,458 --> 00:44:43,760
Well, it's better than leathery old farmer.

75
00:44:43,960 --> 00:44:48,307
All skin and bone, he was. I'm still
picking bits of him out of me teeth.

76
00:44:48,507 --> 00:44:49,516
[TOM SNEEZES]

77
00:44:49,716 --> 00:44:52,811
Well, that's lovely, that is. A floater.

78
00:44:53,011 --> 00:44:54,896
WILLIAM:
Might improve the flavor.

79
00:44:55,096 --> 00:44:57,649
Ah. There's more where that came from.

80
00:44:57,849 --> 00:44:59,141
- Oh, no, you don't!
TOM: Ow!

81
00:44:59,434 --> 00:45:02,863
[TOM WHIMPERING]

82
00:45:03,063 --> 00:45:04,980
Sit down!

83
00:45:06,817 --> 00:45:08,692
[SNEEZES]

84
00:45:08,944 --> 00:45:10,945
[TOM BLOWING NOSE]

85
00:45:13,114 --> 00:45:17,294
Well, I hope you're gonna gut these nags.

86
00:45:17,494 --> 00:45:20,246
I don't like the stinky parts.

87
00:45:20,497 --> 00:45:23,300
- Ow!
- I said sit down.

88
00:45:23,500 --> 00:45:24,509
I'm starving!

89
00:45:24,709 --> 00:45:27,763
Now, are we having horse tonight or what?

90
00:45:27,963 --> 00:45:32,007
BERT: Shut your cakehole.
You'll eat what I'll give you.

91
00:45:32,884 --> 00:45:36,563
WILLIAM: How come he's the cook?
Everything tastes the same.

92
00:45:36,763 --> 00:45:38,315
Everything tastes like chicken.

93
00:45:38,515 --> 00:45:39,691
TOM:
Except the chicken.

94
00:45:39,891 --> 00:45:41,193
WILLIAM:
What tastes like fish!

95
00:45:41,393 --> 00:45:44,655
I'm just saying,
a little appreciation would be nice.

96
00:45:44,855 --> 00:45:46,230
[PONY NEIGHS]

97
00:45:47,065 --> 00:45:50,786
Oh. "Thank you very much, Bert.
Lovely stew, Bert."

98
00:45:50,986 --> 00:45:54,947
- How hard is that?
- Shh. Shh, shh. Shh.

99
00:45:55,407 --> 00:45:58,200
BERT:
Just needs a sprinkle of squirrel dung.

100
00:45:59,327 --> 00:46:01,245
Here, that's my grog.

101
00:46:01,454 --> 00:46:03,706
[TOM WHIMPERS]

102
00:46:03,915 --> 00:46:06,876
Sorry. Ow!

103
00:46:08,795 --> 00:46:13,007
Ooh. That is beautifully balanced, that is.

104
00:46:13,633 --> 00:46:16,594
Wrap your laughing gear around that, eh?

105
00:46:17,345 --> 00:46:18,596
Good, isn't it?

106
00:46:18,930 --> 00:46:20,315
[BERT CHUCKLES]

107
00:46:20,515 --> 00:46:23,058
That's why I'm the cook.

108
00:46:23,518 --> 00:46:25,269
[WILLIAM GRUNTS]

109
00:46:30,817 --> 00:46:34,996
WILLIAM: Oh, me guts are grumbling.
I got to snaffle something.

110
00:46:35,196 --> 00:46:37,948
- Flesh, I need flesh.
TOM: Ah! Ah!

111
00:46:38,491 --> 00:46:39,909
[TOM BLOWS NOSE]

112
00:46:40,243 --> 00:46:42,494
[SCREAMS]
Blimey!

113
00:46:43,246 --> 00:46:46,091
Bert. Bert!
Look what's come out of me hooter.

114
00:46:46,291 --> 00:46:48,417
It's got arms and legs and everything.

115
00:46:48,752 --> 00:46:50,178
BERT:
What is it?

116
00:46:50,378 --> 00:46:53,047
I don't know.
But I don't like the way it wriggles around.

117
00:46:57,052 --> 00:47:00,230
What are you, then? An oversized squirrel?

118
00:47:00,430 --> 00:47:02,107
I'm a burglar-- Uh, Hobbit.

119
00:47:02,307 --> 00:47:04,359
A burglarobbit?

120
00:47:04,559 --> 00:47:06,153
Can we cook him?

121
00:47:06,353 --> 00:47:08,896
We can try.

122
00:47:11,691 --> 00:47:13,744
He wouldn't make more than a mouthful.

123
00:47:13,944 --> 00:47:16,705
Not when he's skinned and boned.

124
00:47:16,905 --> 00:47:19,875
Perhaps there's more burglarobbits
around these parts.

125
00:47:20,075 --> 00:47:23,118
Might be enough for a pie.

126
00:47:23,370 --> 00:47:25,338
- Grab him!
TOM: He's too quick.

127
00:47:25,538 --> 00:47:28,842
WILLIAM:
Right. Come here, you little--

128
00:47:29,042 --> 00:47:30,384
Gotcha.

129
00:47:30,585 --> 00:47:34,181
Are there any more of you little fellas
hiding where you shouldn't?

130
00:47:34,381 --> 00:47:35,965
No.

131
00:47:36,216 --> 00:47:37,517
He's lying.

132
00:47:37,717 --> 00:47:42,022
- No, I'm not!
- Hold his toes over the fire.

133
00:47:42,222 --> 00:47:44,932
Make him squeal!

134
00:47:45,392 --> 00:47:46,976
[SQUEALS]

135
00:47:48,395 --> 00:47:49,404
Drop him!

136
00:47:49,604 --> 00:47:51,021
You what?

137
00:47:51,815 --> 00:47:53,273
I said...

138
00:47:53,566 --> 00:47:54,576
...drop him.

139
00:47:54,776 --> 00:47:56,119
[GROWLS]

140
00:47:56,319 --> 00:47:57,569
[BILBO YELLS]

141
00:47:58,738 --> 00:48:00,739
[ALL YELLING]

142
00:48:12,335 --> 00:48:13,919
[TOM SQUEALS]

